A member of the House of Representatives, Saidu Musa Abdul, has said there is need to educate Nigerians about the constitutional duties of a legislator at both federal and state levels. Speaking on plans and programmes of the 9th House of Representatives, he said many Nigerians don’t have a clear knowledge of the duties of a legislator which is to make laws that will better their lives. Abdul who is the member representing Bida/Gbako/Katcha federal constituency of Niger State said: “It is time we start raising awareness on some of the responsibilities that come with the offices. People can hardly draw a line between the role of an executive and what a legislator is expected to do,” he said. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Group sensitizes youth on role of legislators The legislature as toll gate Does a Nigerian lawmaker earn more than US President Trump?